entry.content:
Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.content: ... that Céline Dept (pictured) was the first Belgian YouTuber to reach 10 million subscribers?

entry.title: Operation Matterhorn logistics (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Operation Matterhorn logistics involved the construction of airfields in China by thousands of laborers with hammers and wicker baskets?

entry.content: ... that after qualifying for the 2024 Summer Olympics at the age of 11, skateboarder Zheng Haohao became the youngest Chinese sportsperson to participate in the Olympics?

entry.title: Mariesa Crow (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that electrical engineering professor Mariesa Crow raises alpacas?

entry.title: medals at the 1964 Summer Olympics (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Larisa Latynina became the most-medalled Olympian after she won six medals at the 1964 Summer Olympics?

entry.title: her debut album (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that South African singer Tyla delayed her debut album's submission date in order to collaborate with Tems?

entry.title: Jenya Kazbekova (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Jenya Kazbekova, a competition climber on Ukraine's 2024 Olympic team, is the daughter and granddaughter of competition climbing medalists?

entry.title: The boys of Pointe du Hoc (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that when delivering his speech "The boys of Pointe du Hoc" on the 40th anniversary of the Normandy landings, Ronald Reagan addressed 62 veteran service members present on D-Day?
